#: ../../P/prime-time.rst:5
msgid "prime time"
msgstr "prime time"

#: ../../P/prime-time.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../P/prime-time.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from TV programming] Normal high-usage hours on a system or network. Back "
"in the days of big timesharing machines ‘prime time’ was when lots of people"
" were competing for limited cycles, usually the day shift. Avoidance of "
"prime time was traditionally given as a major reason for :ref:`night-mode` "
"hacking. The term fell into disuse during the early PC era, but has been "
"revived to refer to times of day or evening at which the Internet tends to "
"be heavily loaded, making Web access slow. The hackish tendency to late-"
"night :ref:`hacking-run`\\s has changed not a bit."
msgstr ""
"[テレビの番組編成から]システムやネットワーク上の、通常の高使用時間帯。大型タイムシェアリングマシンの時代には、‘prime "
"time’は多くの人が限られたサイクルを奪い合っているとき、たいていは日勤帯だった。prime timeを避けることは、伝統的に\\ "
":ref:`night-mode`\\ "
"ハッキングの主な理由として挙げられた。この用語はPC時代の初期に使われなくなったが、インターネットが重く負荷され、Webアクセスが遅くなる時間帯や晩を指すために復活した。深夜の\\"
" :ref:`hacking-run`\\ へのハッカー的な傾向は少しも変わっていない。"
